%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Dune%3A%20Part%20Two'%20is%20a%20Cautionary%20Tale%20on%20Hero%20Worship%2C%20Rooted%20in%20a%20Tragic%20Love%20Story%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03110552%2FUntitled-design-1-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20there%20were%20doubts%20that%20director%20Denis%20Villeneuve%E2%80%99s%20adaptation%20of%20Frank%20Herbert%E2%80%99s%20totemic%201965%20source%20material%20was%20another%20series%20on%20the%20white%20saviour%20complex%20(like%20at%20least%20a%20few%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thewrap.com%2Fdune-tired-tropes-white-savior-middle-east-muslim%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eop-eds%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20suggested%20after%20the%20first%20part%2C%20despite%20overwhelming%20evidence%20to%20the%20contrary)%2C%20he%20takes%20good%20care%20of%20it%20in%20the%20sequel.%20In%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDune%3A%20Part%20Two%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Villeneuve%20is%20less%20subtle%20with%20his%20choices%2C%20being%20aggressively%20vocal%20about%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20intent%2C%20leaving%20very%20little%20room%20for%20ambiguity.%20If%20anything%2C%20Villeneuve%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDune%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20films%20are%20an%20indictment%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98messiah%E2%80%99%20narrative%2C%20just%20like%20Herbert%20intended.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FU2Qp5pL3ovA%3Fsi%3DVJf9eE6tCDoezT5F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20end%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDune%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2021)%20saw%20Paul%20Atreides%20(Timothee%20Chalamet)%20join%20the%20Fremen%20%E2%80%93%20the%20natives%20of%20Arrakis%20%E2%80%93%20after%20his%20father%20(Oscar%20Isaac)%20and%20army%20was%20wiped%20out%20by%20the%20Harkonnens%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20single%20night.%20Paul%20is%20a%20%E2%80%98special%E2%80%99%20boy%2C%20or%20so%20it%20appears%20to%20most%20of%20us.%20Born%20in%20royalty%2C%20raised%20by%20a%20mother%20who%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Bene%20Gesserit%20%E2%80%93%20a%20secret%20order%20of%20sisterhood%20making%20strategic%20alliances%20across%20the%20galaxy%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20he%20has%20visions%20of%20possible%20futures.%20Villeneuve%20paints%20Paul%20as%20someone%20haunted%20by%20the%20gifts%20he%E2%80%99s%20bestowed%20with%2C%20visibly%20shaken%20by%20his%20dreams%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98holy%20war%E2%80%99%20taking%20place%20in%20his%20name.%20It%E2%80%99s%20easy%20to%20believe%20Paul%E2%80%99s%20moral%20conundrum%20because%20of%20the%20actor%20(Chalamet)%20selling%20it.%20Like%20Chani%20(Zendaya)%20reasons%20to%20a%20fellow%20fighter%20about%20why%20she%E2%80%99s%20rooting%20for%20Paul%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CHe%E2%80%99s%20sincere%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes%2C%20something%20one%20could%20also%20extend%20to%20Chalamet%20himself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20he%20enters%20Sietch%20Tabr%20%E2%80%93%20the%20home%20of%20the%20Fremen%20%E2%80%93%20Paul%20senses%20murmurs%20how%20they%20view%20him%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELisan%20al%20Gaib%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20the%20%E2%80%98saviour%E2%80%99%20who%20will%20turn%20Arrakis%2C%20a%20desert%20planet%2C%20into%20a%20green%20paradise.%20Initially%20reluctant%20to%20embrace%20the%20prophecy%2C%20Paul%20insists%20on%20wanting%20to%20learn%20the%20Fremen%20ways%2C%20so%20he%20can%20join%20them%20in%20their%20war%20against%20Harkonnens%2C%20and%20thereby%20avenge%20his%20father.%20The%20Fremen%20carry%20out%20covert%20operations%2C%20systematically%20dismantling%20the%20Harkonnens%E2%80%99%20spice%20production.%20During%20these%20scenes%2C%20Villeneuve%20uses%20the%20idiom%20of%20a%20war%20film%20%E2%80%93%20where%20cinematographer%20Grieg%20Fraser%20chases%20the%20characters%20as%20they%20escape%20gunfire%20and%20explosions%2C%20bringing%20an%20immediacy%20to%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20luminous%20things%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDune%3A%20Part%20Two%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20is%20how%20Villeneuve%20controls%20the%20rhythm%20here.%20Even%20with%20a%20168-minute%20runtime%2C%20which%20might%20invite%20a%20few%20groans%2C%20the%20sequel%20runs%20smoothly%20for%20the%20most%20part.%20Like%20in%20a%20scene%20when%20Paul%20and%20Chani%20glide%20on%20sand%20side%20by%20side%2C%20like%20the%20perfectly%20synchronised%2C%20newly-minted%20lovers.%20Despite%20many%20elaborate%20action%20set-pieces%20that%20make%20it%20a%20spectacle%2C%20Villeneuve%20stops%20time%20in%20key%20scenes%2C%20allowing%20us%20to%20fully%20immerse%20ourselves%20into%20the%20shoes%20of%20the%20characters%2C%20to%20feel%20their%20love%2C%20fear%2C%20survival%20instinct%20and%20betrayal.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20choice%20by%20a%20secure%20filmmaker%2C%20who%20knows%20people%20won%E2%80%99t%20mind%20the%20runtime%20as%20long%20as%20it%20remains%20compelling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03110637%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-11.00.09%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x497.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03110637%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-11.00.09%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x497.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03110637%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-11.00.09%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x146.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03110637%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-11.00.09%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699855%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22408%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20%E2%80%98Dune%3A%20Part%20Two%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20a%20film%20meditating%20on%20the%20exploitative%20ways%20of%20organised%20religion%2C%20the%20ruthless%20nature%20of%20colonial%20oppression%20%5Ba%20scene%20showing%20Harkonnens%20bombing%20the%20Fremen%20Citadel%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20evacuate%20and%20head%20south%2C%20looked%20eerily%20like%20Israel%20bombing%20Gaza%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months%5D%20and%20wasteful%20ways%20of%20a%20capitalist%20society%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20Paul%20and%20Chani%E2%80%99s%20doomed%20love%20story%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20Villeneuve%E2%80%99s%20epic%20film.%20Chani%2C%20while%20slowly%20getting%20charmed%20by%20Paul%E2%80%99s%20earnestness%2C%20keeps%20insisting%20that%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20give%20in%20to%20his%20messianic%20visions%20where%20he%20turns%20into%20a%20mass%20murderer.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20startling%20conflict%2C%20where%20a%20girl%20falls%20in%20love%20with%20someone%20who%20claims%20will%20enslave%20her%20people%2C%20maintaining%20that%20one%20can%20always%20mend%20their%20fate%20with%20their%20actions.%20Torn%20up%20about%20how%20Paul%20is%20counselled%20by%20his%20mother%20(Rebecca%20Ferguson)%20about%20embracing%20the%20prophecy%2C%20how%20people%20like%20Stiglar%20(Javier%20Bardem)%20blindly%20inflict%20their%20faith%20on%20him%20to%20%E2%80%98lead%20them%20to%20paradise%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20Chani%20is%20the%20only%20one%20who%20sees%20in%20Paul%20a%20troubled%20man%20worth%20saving.%20Spaihts%20and%20Villeneuve%20introduce%20a%20nice%20touch%2C%20when%20Chani%20slaps%20Paul%20after%20he%20endangers%20himself%20by%20consuming%20the%20Water%20of%20Life%20%E2%80%93%20a%20poison%20extracted%20from%20a%20sand%20worm.%20It%20tells%20us%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98equality%E2%80%99%20of%20their%20dynamic%2C%20where%20she%20won%E2%80%99t%20waste%20a%20second%20to%20bring%20him%20down%20from%20the%20pedestal%20others%20have%20built%20for%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDune%3A%20Part%20Two%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20becomes%20partially%20less%20interesting%20in%20parts%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20because%20of%20the%20high%20standards%20Villeneuve%20and%20Co.%20set%20by%20themselves.%20The%20Harkonnens%2C%20who%20were%20beautifully%20eerie%20and%20gothic%20in%20the%20first%20part%2C%20are%20left%20without%20too%20many%20dimensions%20here.%20Rabben%20(Dave%20Bautista)%20runs%20around%20like%20a%20clueless%20general%20as%20the%20Fremen%20categorically%20attack%20his%20spice%20gathering%20machines%20and%20kill%20his%20people.%20Feyd%20Rautha%20(Austin%20Butler)%2C%20described%20as%20psychotic%2C%20goes%20on%20to%20amount%20to%20less%20than%20satisfactory%2C%20despite%20a%20gorgeous%20entry%20sequence%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20inspired%20by%20Leni%20Reifenstahl%E2%80%99s%20dazzling%20scale.%20Vladimir%20Harkonnen%20(Stellan%20Skarsgard)%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20the%20main%20antagonist%20of%20the%20first%20part%20%E2%80%93%20has%20little%20to%20do%20apart%20from%20bark%20threats%20or%20play%20sadistic%20games%20with%20his%20nephews.%20The%20Emperor%20(Christopher%20Walken)%20and%20Princess%20(Florence%20Pugh)%20too%20have%20not%20much%20to%20do%20in%20this%20dense%20narrative.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20some%20of%20the%20most%20daring%20visuals%20in%20a%20recent%20film%2C%20Villeneuve%20ensures%20that%20even%20those%20unfamiliar%20with%20the%20earlier%20film%20can%20keep%20up%3B%20Dune%3A%20Part%20Two%20stands%20on%20its%20own%20legs.%20Its%20most%20thrilling%20when%20it%20puts%20its%20audience%20on%20top%20of%20a%20sand%20worm%2C%20blowing%20through%20the%20sand%2C%20with%20exquisite%20sound%20design%20(by%20Alexis%20Feodoroof%2C%20Ron%20Bartlett)%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20superbly%20simulated%20to%20feel%20like%20an%20amusement%20park%20ride%20%E2%80%93%20not%20the%20worst%20thing%20a%20franchise%20film%20could%20be%2C%20despite%20what%20Martin%20Scorsese%20has%20said.%20In%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20closing%20moments%2C%20a%20coronation%20ceremony%20feels%20like%20it%20is%20painted%20with%20an%20ominous%20hue%20instead%20of%20feeling%20triumphant.%20The%20ascendancy%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98hero%E2%80%99%2C%20something%20we%E2%80%99re%20conditioned%20to%20cheer%20for%20as%20viewers%2C%20feels%20like%20a%20blade%20through%20the%20heart.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDune%3A%20Part%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20concludes%20with%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20holy%20war%2C%20just%20like%20the%20prophecy%20stated%2C%20leaving%20us%20with%20a%20heavy%20silence%20about%20how%20power%20invariably%20corrupts.%20Rousing%20chants%20like%20%E2%80%98Long%20live%20the%20fighters%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20single%20person%E2%80%99s%20ego%2C%20is%20enough%20to%20fuel%20wars%20for%20decades%2C%20centuries.%20Nobody%20wins%2C%20or%20as%20the%20reverend%20mother%20(Charlotte%20Rampling)%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20no%20sides.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709444286000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03110552%2FUntitled-design-1-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fdune-part-two-is-a-cautionary-tale-on-hero-worship-rooted-in-a-tragic-love-story%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Denis%20Villeneuve%20ensures%20that%20the%20film%20is%20not%20just%20for%20fans%20of%20the%20franchise%20but%20also%20stands%20on%20it%20own.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fdune-part-two-is-a-cautionary-tale-on-hero-worship