ds%2F2024%2F03%2F03093209%2FThe-Moral-Contagion..jpg%20887w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699831%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20Moral%20Contagion%E2%80%99%20by%20Julia%20Hauser%20and%20Sarnath%20Banerjee%2C%20HarperCollins%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Moral%20Contagion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Julia%20Hauser%20and%20Sarnath%20Banerjee%20find%20in%20history%20a%20home%20for%20the%20years%20we%20lived%20with%20COVID-19.%20In%20the%20course%20of%20nine%20chapters%2C%20illustrated%20by%20Banerjee%2C%20the%20smallness%20and%20the%20bigness%20of%20collective%20disease%20travels%20through%20time.%20A%20history%20lecturer%2C%20Hauser%20tells%20the%20stories%20of%20forgotten%20and%20enormous%20suffering%20in%20Constantinople%2C%20in%20Florence%2C%20in%20Granada%2C%20in%20Aleppo%2C%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20in%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20in%20Johannesburg%20in%20a%20sage%2C%20conversational%20way.%20It%20acts%20as%20succour.%20It%20makes%20our%20current%20age%20feel%20less%20wretched.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20offers%20lightly%20that%20administrative%20politics%20that%20thrives%20on%20the%20disavowal%20of%20the%20plague%20appears%20to%20unite%20plagues%20across%20the%20ages.%20As%20does%20the%20discomfort%20of%20rulers%20and%20emperors%20with%20disease.%20Having%20pronounced%20themselves%20god%E2%80%99s%20own%20chosen%20ones%2C%20an%20event%20requiring%20them%20to%20step%20up%20%E2%80%93%20with%20very%20little%20cooperation%20from%20that%20very%20god%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20brutal%20reckoning%20of%20their%20own%20incapacities.%20Faced%20with%20fevers%20and%20deaths%2C%20rulers%E2%80%99%20powerlessness%20is%20direct%20mockery%20of%20their%20pronouncements.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%2C%20too%2C%20is%20not%20spun%20as%20a%20grand%20folly%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20only%20human%2C%20the%20book%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20full%20strength%20of%20something%20as%20all-swallowing%20as%20a%20pandemic%20is%20often%20too%20much%20to%20take%2C%20too%20enormous%20to%20comprehend.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHauser%20cites%20various%20rulers%20who%20declared%20the%20end%20of%20a%20plague%20by%20royal%20decree%20only%20to%20suffer%20three%20more%20decades%20of%20it%20%E2%80%93%20like%20Byzantine%20emperor%20Justinian.%20Indians%20under%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20rule%20will%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fwe-are-in-the-endgame-of-covid-19-pandemic-in-india-harsh-vardhan%2Farticleshow%2F81378288.cms%5C%22%3Ecelebrations%20of%20late%202020%20and%20early%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20just%20before%20a%20crushing%20second%20wave%20hit.%20It%20is%20this%20temporal%20enormity%20that%20Hauser%20doffs%20her%20hat%20to%2C%20in%20the%20book.%20She%20draws%20a%20line%20through%20histories%20she%20is%20familiar%20with%20or%20has%20pushed%20herself%20to%20be%20familiar%20with%20%E2%80%93%20offering%20no%20grand%20philosophy%20to%20justify%20diseases%20and%20death%20but%20only%20graspable%20stories%20on%20their%20effect%2C%20impact%20and%20the%20petty%20cruelties%20they%20inspired.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHauser%E2%80%99s%20is%20not%20the%20only%20book%20that%20has%20done%20it%20in%20recent%20times%20%E2%80%93%20Orhan%20Pamuk%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ENights%20of%20Plague%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20serves%20the%20same%20purpose%20%E2%80%93%20but%20its%20grand%20sweep%20through%20time%20sets%20it%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fcovid-deaths-grief%5C%22%3EWhy%20I%20Don%E2%80%99t%20Believe%20it%E2%80%99s%20Time%20to%20%E2%80%98Move%20on%E2%80%99%20From%20Covid%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20book%20entirely%20built%20of%20resonances.%20%3C%2Fspa