which%20collects%20the%20most%20rain%2C%20Lakda%20continued%20to%20plant%20%E2%80%98Annapurna%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20modern%20hybrid%20variety%20of%20rice%2C%20which%20she%20referred%20as%20%3Ci%3Esarkaari%20dhaan%20(%3C%2Fi%3Egovernment%20rice).%20In%20the%20%3Cem%3Eguda%20(%3C%2Fem%3Eupland)%2C%20she%20had%20gone%20back%20to%20growing%20the%20crops%20of%20her%20ancestors%20%E2%80%93%20indigenous%2C%20or%20heirloom%20rice%20varieties%20called%20Kalamaliphool%2C%20Bahalguda%2C%20Lusri%20and%20Luhini.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20native%20seed%20varieties%2C%20which%20have%20survived%20several%20environmental%20vagaries%20in%20their%20evolutionary%20history%20do%20better%20in%20unpredictable%20weather%20and%20ensure%20food%20security%2C%20say%20farmers.%20They%20also%20help%20stave%20off%20the%20escalating%20costs%20of%20input-intensive%20modern%20hybrid%20varieties%20of%20rice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20middle%2C%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20we%20lost%20many%20of%20our%20older%20rice%20seeds%2C%20and%20the%20seeds%20had%20got%20mixed%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20recounted%20Lakda%2C%20in%20the%20courtyard%20of%20her%20hut%20sheltered%20by%20a%20tamarind%20tree%20in%20the%20interior%20Kalumara%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThen%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20started%20growing%20traditional%20rice%20again%20as%20it%20grows%20without%20chemical%20fertilisers%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02165854%2F2-5.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02165854%2F2-5.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02165854%2F2-5-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02165854%2F2-5-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699769%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHeirloom%20or%20traditional%20seeds%20of%20rice%20such%20as%20Lusri%20rice%20are%20hardy%2C%20and%20adapt%20well%20to%20rainfall%20shortages%20and%20they%20prefer%20its%20taste%2C%20say%20Adivasi%20farmers%20in%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Subdega.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Lakda%20enjoys%20the%20most%20is%20the%20taste%20of%20these%20rice%20varities.%20%E2%80%9CLusri%20(a%20brown%20rice)%20is%20delicious%20even%20if%20you%20%5Bit%5D%20eat%20two%20days%20later%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20Along%20with%20planting%20four%20native%20rice%20varieties%2C%20Lakda%20grows%20gourds%2C%20kurthi%20(black%20gram)%2C%20urad%20lentils%20as%20she%20%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9Ccannot%20afford%20to%20buy%20dal%20otherwise%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20next%20block%2C%20Balisankara%E2%80%99s%20Kakerjor%20village%2C%20Kamalsagar%20Kullu%2C%20a%20young%20farmer%2C%20dressed%20in%20a%20T-shirt%20and%20shorts%2C%C2%A0was%20returning%20after%20working%20in%20his%20fields.%20He%20also%20did%20not%20let%20go%20of%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20heirloom%20rice%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKullu%20readily%20spoke%20of%20the%20rice%20varieties%20he%20grows%20%E2%80%93%20Sariyaguda%2C%20Kaniaaguda%2C%20Juiguda%2C%20Budhaguda%3Ci%3E%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fi%3Ewhich%20survived%20even%20when%20the%20monsoons%20wavered%20and%20ensured%20grains%20for%20the%20family.%20There%20were%20also%20varieties%20such%20as%20%3Ci%3EKolamaliphool%3C%2Fi%3E%20that%20survived%20excess%20water%20from%20flooding%2C%20said%20Kullu%2C%20explaining%20the%20unique%20resilience%20and%20adaptability%20of%20the%20varieties%20he%20preferred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThen%2C%20there%20are%20rice%20plants%20that%20develop%20a%20red-coloured%20sheath%20which%20are%20high%20in%20medicinal%20properties%E2%80%A6%20Our%20elders%20say%2C%20%3Ci%3EKalawati%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20%3Ci%3ELuchai%3C%2Fi%3E%20are%20good%20to%20eat%20as%20they%20help%20control%20blood%20sugar%20levels%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecognising%20Kullu%E2%80%99s%20efforts%2C%20the%20state%20government%20had%20awarded%20him%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbest%20organic%20farmer%E2%80%9D%20award%20at%20a%20district%20level%20event%20in%202016%20but%20he%20did%20not%20receive%20any%20other%20state%20assistance%20since%20then.%20Yet%2C%20he%20continued%20his%20way%20of%20cropping.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170111%2F3-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170111%2F3-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170111%2F3-2-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170111%2F3-2-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699771%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKalamsagar%20Kullu%20has%20shared%20seeds%20with%2050%20other%20farmers%20in%20neighbouring%20villages%20where%20the%20native%20seeds%20were%20no%20longer%20available.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20%5Bquantity%20of%20the%5D%20produce%20from%20the%20traditional%20seeds%20and%20practices%20is%20a%20bit%20lower%20compared%20to%20modern%20hybrid%20varieties%2C%20it%20is%20true%2C%20but%20our%20own%20rice%20seeds%20sprout%20even%20when%20the%20rains%20fail%2C%20or%20even%20when%20the%20rain%20lasts%20a%20brief%20spell%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kullu%20said.%20He%20claimed%20to%20have%20distributed%20the%20indigenous%20seeds%20to%2050%20other%20farming%20families%20in%20the%20vicinity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20necessary%20diversity%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERice%2C%20now%20a%20staple%20of%20a%20majority%20of%20Indians%2C%20was%20domesticated%20in%20the%20broad%20region%20from%20the%20foothills%20of%20the%20Eastern%20Himalayas%20in%20India%20to%20China%20about%206%2C500-7%2C000%20years%20ago.%20While%20its%20primacy%20as%20occupying%20the%20largest%20area%20among%20all%20food%20crops%20continues%2C%20over%20the%20past%20five%20decades%2C%20it%20underwent%20an%20irreversible%20genetic%20erosion%2C%20with%20the%20disappearance%20of%20thousands%20of%20native%20rice%20seed%20varieties%20from%20farms%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHalf%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20more%20than%201%2C10%2C000%20distinct%20varieties%20of%20rice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkarnataka%2Ffrom-110000-varieties-of-rice-to-only-6000-now%2Farticle3284453.ece%5C%22%3Egrew%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%2C%20plant%20scientist%20R.H.%20Richharia%20noted.%20These%20included%20rice%20that%20could%20survive%20on%20dry%20land%20farms%20without%20irrigation%2C%20deep-water%20farms%20and%20those%20which%20could%20withstand%20saline%20water%20on%20coastal%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20advent%20of%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20meant%20the%20government%20subsidised%20and%20heavily%20promoted%20a%20few%20imported%20high-yielding%20varieties%2C%20based%20on%20applying%20petrochemical%20inputs%2C%20such%20as%20pesticides%20and%20fertilisers.%20Within%20years%2C%20the%20number%20of%20native%20rice%20landraces%20that%20took%20thousands%20of%20years%20to%20evolve%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DdcI_L9stV6k%5C%22%3Edwindled%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20over%20one%20lakh%20to%20around%206%2C000%2C%20a%20loss%20of%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20indigenous%20rice%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%202023%20study%20by%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.cseindia.org%2Fattachments%2F0.87846400_1706003284_cover-story-nutrient.pdf%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20green%20revolution%E2%80%99s%20breeding%20programmes%20%E2%80%93%20focused%20on%20high-yielding%20varieties%20%E2%80%93%20have%20resulted%20in%20worsening%20the%20staple%20grain%E2%80%99s%20nutrients%2C%20zinc%20and%20iron%20had%20decreased%20by%2033%25%20and%2027%25%20in%20rice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20traditional%20varieties%20were%20neglected%20as%20low%20yielders%2C%20that%20lodge%20and%20mature%20late%2C%20rice%20conservationists%20contend%20that%20this%20was%20not%20true%20for%20all%20native%20varieties.%20Dr%20Anupam%20Paul%2C%20who%20has%20promoted%20400%20native%20rice%20varieties%20working%20as%20a%20rice%20conservationist%20in%20Fulia%20district%20in%20West%20Bengal%20and%20worked%20for%2030%20years%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20office%2C%20says%20considering%20all%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20as%20having%20less%20yield%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20over-simplification%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20like%20declaring%20all%20Indians%20are%20naked%20%3Cem%3Efakirs%3C%2Fem%3E%20(beggars)%20or%20all%20Indians%20are%20black%20skinned.%20It%20merely%20satisfied%20the%20foreign%20bosses%20and%20accommodated%20chemical%20intensive%20farming%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Paul%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20narrow%20focus%20on%20rice%20yield%20alone%20wiped%20out%20thousands%20of%20seed%20varieties%2C%20destroyed%20rice%E2%80%99s%20diversified%20gene%20pool%2C%20and%20made%20soils%20unproductive%20over%20the%20long%20term.%20Now%2C%20with%20worsening%20climate%20change%2C%20it%20means%20lower%20resilience%20as%20several%20of%20the%20native%20seeds%2C%20selected%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20ancient%20cultivators%20over%20centuries%2C%20possessed%20the%20ability%20to%20adapt%20and%20grow%20as%20per%20the%20local%20ecological%20niches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Dr%20Debal%20Deb%2C%20an%20agro-ecologist%20who%20set%20up%20a%20seed%20bank%20in%20Odisha%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fthe-struggle-to-save-heirloom-rice-in-india%2F%5C%22%3E2019%20essay%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Scientific%20American%20has%20documented%20landraces%20growing%20in%20the%20regions%20of%20Odisha%2C%20Bengal%2C%20Jharkhand%20such%20as%20Lakshmi%20dighal%2C%20Rani%20kajal%20and%20Jabra%20which%20can%20elongate%20their%20stems%20as%20floodwaters%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20rice%20varieties%20like%20Matla%2C%20Getu%20and%20Kallurundai%20can%20grow%20even%20on%20saline%20soil%20and%20survive%20incursion%20of%20rising%20sea%20levels.%20Deb%20explained%20that%20in%20a%20drought%2C%20indigenous%20varieties%20of%20Kelas%2C%20Rangi%2C%20Gadaba%2C%20Kaya%20may%20give%20greater%20yields%20than%20even%20the%20modern%20HYVs%20(High%20Yielding%20Varieties).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20such%20as%20Dudhe%20Bolta%20and%20Garib-Sal%20rice%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.academia.edu%2F96317089%2FA_profile_of_heavy_metals_in_rice_Oryza_sativa_ssp_indica_landraces%5C%22%3Eabundant%3C%2Fa%3E%20micronutrients%20such%20as%20iron%20and%20zinc.%20The%20traditional%20landraces%2C%20thus%2C%20hold%20the%20capacity%20to%20provide%20reliable%20means%20of%20providing%20food%20security%20to%20smallholder%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disappearance%20of%20these%20indigenous%20crops%20is%20accompanied%20by%20the%20loss%20of%20knowledge%20and%20expertise%20of%20identifying%20and%20cultivating%20these%20native%20varieties%2C%20which%20include%20hundreds%20of%20aromatic%20varieties%2C%20those%20with%20medicinal%20properties%2C%20rich%20in%20specific%20nutrients%2C%20and%20crucially%2C%20the%20plasticity%20to%20adapt%20to%20unpredictable%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Taste%20of%20spring%20in%20one%E2%80%99s%20mouth%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20hamlets%20nestled%20inside%20Sundargarh%E2%80%99s%20sal%20forests%2C%20farmers%20identified%20dozens%20of%20varieties%20of%20rice%20their%20ancestors%20had%20grown%20for%20years%2C%20categorising%20them%20by%20their%20appearance%2C%20qualities%2C%20level%20of%20land%20they%20thrive%20on%2C%20and%20the%20corresponding%20water%20needs.%20Farmers%20in%20northern%20Odisha%20referred%20to%20the%20low-lying%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3Elands%20that%20collected%20the%20most%20water%20as%20the%20Bahal%2C%20Berna%20in%20which%20grew%20the%20longer%20duration%20rice%2C%20which%20was%20the%20most%20nutritious%2C%20and%20the%20Maal%20and%20Guda%20as%20lands%20on%20which%20they%20grew%20traditional%20rice%20varieties%20that%20needed%20less%20water%2C%20and%20could%20even%20survive%20a%20deficient%20monsoon.%20Farmer%20spoke%20of%20their%20family%E2%80%99s%20rice%20varieties%20and%20why%20they%20were%20preferred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170505%2F4-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170505%2F4-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170505%2F4-1-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02170505%2F4-1-1024x684.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699773%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIndia%20had%20several%20thousands%20of%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice%20till%20the%201970s%2C%20with%20distinct%20properties%20of%20taste%2C%20smell%2C%20climate%20resilience.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20grew%20Machkantha%2C%20Sapri%2C%20Mangraphool%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20sheath%20is%20red%20and%20very%20tasty%20%E2%80%93%20all%20as%20%3Ci%3EBahal%3C%2Fi%3E%20rice.%20We%20grew%20Karagutha%20a%20%3Ci%3EBerna%3C%2Fi%3E%20long%20duration%20rice%2C%20Bhajna%20which%20is%20both%20Bahal%20and%20Berna%2C%20then%20Raigadi%2C%20Kaladhaan(a%20black%20rice)%2C%20Barhasaal%20which%20was%20fragrant%20like%20Basmati%2C%20and%20Lusri%20which%20grows%20in%20less%20water%2C%20and%20Khandsagar%2C%E2%80%9D%20recounted%20Rudra%20Behera%2C%20an%20elderly%20farmer%20in%20Subdega%E2%80%99s%20Mayabahal%20village%2C%20who%20says%20in%20one%20look%20he%20could%20tell%20apart%20all%20these%20different%20rice%20grains%20that%20he%20grew%20up%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20elderly%20farmer%20Ravindra%20Gop%20compared%20the%20taste%20of%20the%20native%20varieties%20such%20as%20Nohachi%20dhaan%20to%20having%20rice%20with%20milk%2C%20so%20fresh%20and%20delicious%2C%20%E2%80%9Cas%20if%20you%20could%20taste%20the%20spring%20in%20your%20mouth%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBehera%20said%20that%20it%20was%20much%20after%20the%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20and%20more%20recently%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%20that%20the%20switch%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfoundation%20dhaan%E2%80%9D%20or%20hybrids%20hastened%20after%20the%20state%20government%20started%20procuring%20rice%20locally%20to%20distribute%20in%20the%20public%20distribution%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EDesi%3C%2Fi%3E%20%5Blocal%5D%20red%20rice%20varieties%20are%20richer%20in%20nutrition%20but%20the%20government%20does%20not%20procure%20%3Ci%3Edesi%20%3C%2Fi%3Evarieties%20%E2%80%93%20red%20rice%20is%20rejected%20in%20procurement%20for%20white%20rice.%20They%20give%20loans%20to%20buy%20hybrids%20varieties%2C%20which%20then%20fetch%20higher%20price%20in%20procurement%2C%E2%80%9D%20Behera%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20neighbouring%20village%20Mayabahal%2C%20Sudharshan%20Toppo%2C%20an%20Adivasi%20farmer%2C%20who%20used%20to%20grow%20the%20hardy%2C%20less-water%20Lusri%2C%20Bhajna%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Khandsagar%20rice%20varieties%2C%20which%20ripen%20in%2090-120%20days%2C%20traced%20the%20turn%20away%20from%20native%20rice%20to%20Rengali%20dam%20canal%E2%80%99s%20irrigation%20water%20reaching%20their%20village%2020%20years%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01174004%2F1-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01174004%2F1-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01174004%2F1-1-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01174004%2F1-1-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699675%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAdivasi%20farmers%20in%20Subdega%20in%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Sundargarh%20are%20reviving%20and%20protecting%20traditional%20varieties%20of%20rice.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20question%20a%20farmer%20growing%20%3Ci%3Edesi%20dhaan%3C%2Fi%3E%20(rice)%20faces%20is%3A%20If%20you%20grow%20%3Ci%3Edesi%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20what%20will%20you%20earn%3F%E2%80%9D%20said%20Veronica%20Dungdung%2C%20a%20social%20activist%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20Subdega%2C%20a%20forested%20area%20on%20the%20border%20of%20Jharkhand%20and%20northern%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDundung%20started%20collecting%20and%20organising%20the%20rice%20varieties%20native%20to%20the%20area%20in%202018%20after%20seeing%20the%20changes%20in%20agrarian%20systems%20and%20life%20around%20her.%20%E2%80%9CI%20feel%20that%20growing%20up%2C%20we%20had%20a%20certain%20food%20self-%20sufficiency%20from%20both%20the%20farm%20and%20the%20forest%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20with%20intensive%20pesticides%2C%20urea%20use%2C%20the%20soil%20fertility%20is%20in%20decline%2C%20and%20the%20forest%20has%20been%20thinned%20out%20and%20extensively%20cleared.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20her%20work%20at%20the%20Samajik%20Seva%20Sadan%2C%20a%20small%20NGO%20that%20she%20had%20founded%2C%20she%20shared%20seeds%20of%2012%20traditional%20varieties%20with%20445%20farmers%20in%20Subdega%20and%20Bargaon%20blocks%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDungdung%20said%20income%20versus%20the%20rising%20costs%20of%20the%20petro-chemical%20inputs%20do%20not%20add%20up%20to%20small%20farmers%E2%80%99%20advantage%20in%20any%20real%20way.%20Moreover%2C%20they%20noticed%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Chybrid%20varieties%20shrivelled%20faster%20and%20collapsed%20when%20the%20rains%20varied%20from%20year%20to%20year%2C%20compared%20to%20our%20traditional%20less%20water%20varieties.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSmall%20farmers%20were%20already%20growing%20it%2C%20but%20market%20pressures%20built%20up.%20But%20our%20livelihoods%20are%20not%20about%20money%20alone%2C%20isn%E2%80%99t%20it%3F%20The%20communities%20here%20already%20grew%20indigenous%20rice%20and%20it%20is%20in%20our%20culture.%20We%20are%20trying%20to%20support%20them%20to%20continue%20it%20and%20to%20revive%20cultivation%20where%20the%20seeds%20have%20totally%20vanished%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CMarket%20determines%20all%20life%20%5Beverything%5D%20these%20days%20%E2%80%93%20what%20we%20eat%2C%20we%20wear.%20%3Ci%3EMarket%20ka%20formula%3C%2Fi%3E%20%5Bthe%20way%20of%20the%20market%5D%20has%20entered%20and%20dominated%20our%20lives%2C%20our%20imagination%20and%20minds.%20But%20that%20cannot%20be%20our%20way%20of%20life%2C%20I%20believe.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJyoti%20Dungdung%2C%20an%20Oraon%20Adivasi%20farmer%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20farmers%20who%20had%20joined%20the%20grassroots%20effort%20to%20revive%20native%20seeds.%20In%20early%20hours%20of%20the%20morning%2C%20%3Ci%3Edhundhuk-dhuk%20dhundhuk-dhuk%3C%2Fi%3E%20(the%20hum%20and%20beat%20of%20the%20rhythmic%20pounding%20of%20brown%20rice)%20in%20a%20%3Ci%3Edheki%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3Efilled%20the%20air%20at%20her%20home%20in%20Karlaghati%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20simple%20wooden%20tool%20is%20used%20in%20rural%20homes%20to%20remove%20the%20husk%20from%20paddy%20to%20make%20rice%2C%20and%20is%20believed%20to%20further%20preserve%20the%20micronutrients%20lost%20in%20the%20abrasive%20large%20scale%20polishing%20of%20rice%20in%20mills.%20Dungdung%20estimated%20that%20she%20usually%20de-husked%20around%2010%20kilograms%20of%20brown%20rice%20in%20an%20hour%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20the%20%3Ci%3Edheki%3C%2Fi%3E%20(an%20agricultural%20tool%20used%20for%20threshing%2C%20to%20separate%20rice%20grains%20from%20their%20outer%20husks)%2C%20to%20eat%20it%20fresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Dungdung%20planted%20Sarno%2C%20a%20hybrid%20rice%20needing%20regular%20chemical%20fertilisers%20to%20sell%20in%20the%20market.%20But%20she%20devoted%20the%20largest%20part%20of%20her%20field%20to%20Lusri%2C%20a%20longer%20duration%20heirloom%20brown%20rice.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20grew%20easily%20without%20chemical%20inputs%20and%20fill%20our%20family%E2%80%99s%20plates%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20the%20best%20part%20is%2C%20it%20feels%20light%20and%20good%20in%20one%E2%80%99s%20stomach.%20Recently%2C%20even%20those%20from%20Rourkela%2C%20Bhubhaneshwar%20who%20have%20diabetes%20have%20started%20reaching%20out%20asking%20for%20this%20rice%20as%20it%20is%20much%20better%20for%20health.%E2%80%9D%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%9CAbandoned%20food%20that%20is%20special%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20state%20border%2C%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20in%20a%20similar%20pattern%2C%20hybrid%20and%20high%20yielding%20varieties%20of%20rice%20are%20ubiquitous%2C%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20crop%20area.%20As%20per%20an%20estimate%2C%20ten%20years%20ago%2C%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnirdprojms.in%2Findex.php%2Fjrd%2Farticle%2Fview%2F100055%5C%22%3Etraditional%20varieties%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20grown%20on%20only%20around%2020%25%20of%20the%20cultivated%20area%20of%20rice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020-21%2C%20Jharkhand%20had%20over%201%2C700%20thousand%20hectares%20under%20rice%20cultivation%2C%20nearly%20eight%20times%20more%20than%20its%20other%20main%20cereals%20of%20maize%20and%20wheat.%20It%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sameti.org%2Fstate_profile.php%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIncrease%2520in%2520paddy%2520productivity%2520(from%2Cha%2520to%25205.90%2520lakhs%2520ha.%5C%22%3Eproduced%3C%2Fa%3E%205%2C1230%20quintals%20of%20paddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20after%20a%20series%20of%20droughts%2C%20they%20faced%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fas-farmers-worry-about-feeding-families-zero-paddy-procurement-in-two-of-jharkhands-drought-hit-districts-8540967%2F%5C%22%3Elowest%20rainfall%20in%20121%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20waiting%20to%20plant%20paddy%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekharif%3C%2Fem%3E%20summer%20season.%20Such%20changes%20in%20weather%20have%20made%20the%20future%20uncertain%20for%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20its%20farmers%20who%20still%20practice%20rain-fed%20farming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20in%20upper%20reaches%20of%20the%20Netarhat%20plateau%2C%20in%20Latehar%2C%20who%20have%20no%20means%20of%20irrigation%20say%20many%20have%20continued%20to%20cultivate%20distinct%20varieties%20of%20traditional%20rice.%20Like%20in%20Odisha%2C%20they%20have%20their%20own%20unique%20landraces%20of%20rice%20that%20have%20a%20unique%20built-in%20resilience%20to%20vagaries%20of%20the%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Sohar%20panchayat%20in%20Latehar%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Emukhiya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chief)%20Magdalih%20Toppo%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Pakripaat%2C%20a%20village%20of%2040%20odd%20Oraon%20Adivasi%20families%20said%20most%20families%20still%20grew%20%3Ci%3Edesi%20or%20dhehaati%20dhaan%20%3C%2Fi%3E(indigenous%20rice).%20She%20named%20ten%20varieties%20of%20%3Ci%3Edehaati%20dhaan%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20that%20are%20suitable%20to%20either%20Taand%20(upland%2C%20with%20less%20water)%2C%20or%20the%20Doin%20(lowland%20with%20more%20water)%20and%20the%20land%20is%20further%20divided%20as%20per%20slope%20and%20fertility%20and%20seeds%20sown%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToppo%20spoke%20of%20growing%20%3Ci%3ERanikajar%20%3C%2Fi%3E(with%20tiny%20grains%2C%20great%20taste%2C%20used%20for%20making%20sweets%20out%20of%20rice%20flour%20on%20festivals)%2C%20%3Ci%3EJeeraphool%2C%20Kanamchopa%2C%20Somphiya%2C%20Kalamdaani%3C%2Fi%3E%20(%3Ci%3EDoin%3C%2Fi%3E%20varieties)%2C%20red%20rice%20such%20as%20%3Ci%3EHardiguda%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20and%20medicinal%20rice%20such%20as%20%3Ci%3EKaranga.%20%3C%2Fi%3EShe%20grew%20multiple%3Ci%3E%20Doin%20%3C%2Fi%3Erice%2C%20along%20with%3Ci%3E%20%3C%2Fi%3Emillets%20of%20%3Ci%3Emadua%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3Egondli%20%3C%2Fi%3Ethat%20survived%20in%20even%20less%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171351%2F5.Panicles-of-Folk-rice.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171351%2F5.Panicles-of-Folk-rice.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171351%2F5.Panicles-of-Folk-rice-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171351%2F5.Panicles-of-Folk-rice-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699778%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPanicles%20of%20various%20folk%20rice.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20homes%20here%20have%20own%20seeds%20since%20generations%2C%20which%20breed%20true%20(allowing%20the%20families%20to%20collect%20the%20seeds%20year%20after%20year).%20We%20do%20not%20have%20to%20buy%20anything%20for%20growing%20these%2C%20and%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20wish%20to%20switch%20to%20hybrids%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explained%20how%20the%20farmers%20collected%20the%20seeds%20for%20the%20next%20year%20from%20the%20center%20of%20the%20plot%2C%20and%20after%20drying%20and%20cleaning%20it%2C%20stored%20it%20carefully%20for%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20then%2C%20everyone%E2%80%99s%20faith%20is%20different%20%E2%80%93%20some%20are%20attracted%20to%20hybrids%20for%20more%20yield%2C%E2%80%9D%20Toppo%20added%20that%20the%20village%20still%20had%20a%20communal%20way%20of%20sharing%20the%20work%20of%20sowing%2C%20and%20mutually%20arrived%20on%20decisions%20such%20as%20how%20much%20they%20would%20pay%20one%20another%20for%20helping%20in%20sowing%2C%20based%20on%20what%20most%20of%20them%20could%20afford.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20for%20example%2C%20for%20Rs%20130%20a%20day%2C%20they%20will%20come%20to%20sow%20my%20fields%2C%20and%20then%20later%20for%20the%20same%2C%20I%20will%20go%20to%20their%20farm%20for%20the%20sowing%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20small%20farmers%20spoke%20of%20their%20own%20families%E2%80%99%20%3Ci%3Edehaati%20dhaan%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETeresa%20Tithio%20who%20was%20picking%20saag%20for%20the%20evening%20meal%20said%20she%20grew%20%3Ci%3EKalamdaani%3C%2Fi%3E%20in%20deep%20water%20land%2C%20and%20%3Ci%3EGuda%3C%2Fi%3E%20varieties%20in%20the%20%3Ci%3Etaand%20%3C%2Fi%3E(upland).%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20no%20means%20of%20irrigation%20here%20in%20%3Ci%3Epathaar%20%3C%2Fi%3E(plateau)%2C%20yet%20the%20traditional%20rice%20grows%2C%20not%20in%20very%20large%20quantities%2C%20but%20it%20grows%20reliably.%20We%20incur%20almost%20no%20costs%20to%20grow%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20traditional%20varieties%20leave%20enough%20paddy%20straw%20for%20fodder%2C%20and%20the%20straw%20is%20used%20to%20grow%20mushroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimprosa%20Saras%2C%20a%20Adivasi%20farmer%20in%20Chormunda%20village%20said%20her%20neighbours%20had%20switched%20to%20hybrids%20%E2%80%9Cas%20these%20grow%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ci%3Ebaal%20%3C%2Fi%3E(panicles%2C%20or%20seed%20clusters)%E2%80%9D%20but%20that%20she%20had%20observed%20how%20compared%20to%20the%20traditional%20the%20hybrid%20varieties%20needed%20more%20labour%2C%20and%20more%20chemical%20inputs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20one%20sees%20one%E2%80%99s%20neighbours%E2%80%99%20fields%2C%20then%20one%20gets%20tempted%20to%20copy%2C%20and%20abandon%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20seeds%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20chemicals%20kill%20the%20worms%20on%20the%20earth%20and%20then%20you%20need%20to%20add%20more%20and%20more%20chemicals.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESohar%20panchayat%2C%20made%20up%20of%20remote%20Adivasi%20habitations%2C%20atop%20the%20Netarhat%20plateau%2C%20has%20waged%20a%20struggle%20against%20forced%20displacement%20for%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20proposed%20firing%20range%20for%20military%20practice%20for%20over%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIgnacio%20Tithio%2C%20an%20elderly%20woman%20in%20the%20village%2C%20who%20was%20among%20the%20leaders%20of%20a%20grassroots%20anti-displacement%20movement%20rued%20about%20what%20was%20being%20lost.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20would%20grow%20the%20rice%20in%20the%20deeper%20water%20areas%20and%20in%20%3Ci%3ETaand%20%3C%2Fi%3E(upland)%20we%20would%20grow%20%3Ci%3Emadua%20gondli%3C%2Fi%3E%20small%20millets%20along%20with%20it%2C%20which%20need%20nothing%20and%20almost%20grow%20on%20their%20own.%20Some%20of%20our%20food%20is%20medicinal%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20we%20feed%20%3Ci%3Emadua%20%3C%2Fi%3E(ragi)%20roti%20to%20anyone%20who%20has%20tuberculosis%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recounted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171126%2F9.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171126%2F9.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171126%2F9-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02171126%2F9-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699776%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIgnacia%20Tithio%2C%20an%20elderly%20farmer%20in%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20Latehar%20recounted%20how%20the%20Munda%2C%20Oraon%20and%20Asur%20Adivasi%20families%20on%20the%20plateau%20grew%20several%20varieties%20of%20rice%20that%20survived%20in%20less%20rain.%20Over%20recent%20years%2C%20several%20seeds%20have%20been%20lost%2C%20she%20said.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20three-four%20years%20back%2C%20many%20stopped%20growing%20%3Ci%3Edesi%20dhaan%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20She%20said%20traders%20from%20Ghagra%2C%20Lohardaga%2C%2040-50%20km%20away%2C%20would%20offer%20new%20seeds%20and%20then%20also%20offer%20to%20purchase%20the%20crop%2C%20promising%20an%20assured%20market%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20left%20the%20%3Ci%3Evishesh%20%3C%2Fi%3E(unique)%2C%20and%20got%20distracted%20by%20other%20varieties.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EAb%20jaise-jaise%20hoshiyar%20ho%20rahein%20hain%2C%20baahri%20gyaan%20bahut%20ho%20gaya%2C%20baahri%20ka%20cheez%20ugaa%20rahein%20h