n%20her%20development%20as%20an%20artist%20and%20activist%2C%20and%20at%20once%20attaches%20and%20detaches%20her%20from%20the%20rock%20%E2%80%98n%E2%80%99%20roll%20music%20context%20(and%20shadow)%20of%20her%20late%20husband%2C%20John%20Lennon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOno%20was%20a%20musician%20in%20her%20own%20right%2C%20having%20studied%20music%20composition%20throughout%20her%20life%20(as%20well%20as%20philosophy%20and%20poetry)%2C%20whereas%20Lennon%20had%20studied%20art.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tate.org.uk%2Fwhats-on%2Ftate-modern%2Fyoko-ono%2Fexhibition-guide%5C%22%3EOno%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20the%20meeting%20of%20their%20minds%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20crossed%20over%20into%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20fields%20%E2%80%A6%20from%20avant-garde%20leftfield%20to%20rock%20%E2%80%99n%E2%80%99%20roll%20leftfield.%20We%20tried%20to%20find%20a%20ground%20that%20was%20interesting%20to%20both%20of%20us.%20And%20we%20both%20got%20excited%20and%20stimulated%20by%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20experiences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOno%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98instructions%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201962%2C%20Ono%20hung%2038%20sheets%20of%20paper%20featuring%20a%20set%20of%20instructions%2C%20written%20in%20calligraphic%20Japanese%20script%2C%20on%20a%20wall%20of%20the%20Sogetsu%20Art%20Centre%20in%20Tokyo.%20No%20artist%20had%20exhibited%20concepts%20for%20artworks%20as%20artworks%20themselves%20before%2C%20so%20the%20show%2C%20Instructions%20for%20Paintings%2C%20was%20the%20first%20exhibition%20of%20conceptual%20art.%20Ono%20elevated%20art%20to%20an%20intensely%20intellectual%20activity%2C%20and%20the%20concept%20of%20art%20above%20its%20physical%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOno%E2%80%99s%20instructions%20also%20democratised%20art%2C%20as%20they%20triggered%20the%20imagination%2C%20thought%20and%20creativity%20of%20the%20audience%20who%20is%20left%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%E2%80%9D%20the%20works%20by%20following%20the%20instructions%20in%20their%20real%20lives.%20This%20can%20be%20done%20by%20anyone%2C%20anywhere%2C%20at%20any%20time%2C%20either%20imaginatively%20or%20physically.%20One%20instruction%20entitled%20Painting%20To%20Be%20Constructed%20In%20Your%20Head%20reads%3A%20%E2%80%9CObserve%20three%20paintings%20carefully.%20Mix%20them%20well%20in%20your%20head.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOno%20self-published%20her%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmonoskop.org%2Fimages%2Farchive%2F6%2F64%2F20190320203953%2521Ono_Yoko_Grapefruit_A_Book_of_Instructions_and_Drawings_2000.pdf%5C%22%3EGrapefruit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20collection%20of%20over%20200%20instructions%2C%20in%201964.%20Many%20of%20them%20are%20scattered%20across%20the%20Tate%20galleries%20for%20visitors%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tate%20show%20suggests%20that%20Ono%E2%80%99s%20work%20is%20a%20form%20of%20%E2%80%9Cparticipatory%20art%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20art%20that%20engages%20audiences%20in%20the%20creative%20process.%20But%20this%20is%20reductive.%20Ono%20saw%20her%20instructions%20as%20encapsulations%20of%20ideas%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.guggenheim-bilbao.eus%2Fen%2Flearn%2Fschools%2Fteachers-guides%2Fthe-idea-in-the-work-of-art-2%5C%22%3Eideas%20as%20stones%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cthrown%20into%20the%20water%20for%20ripples%20to%20be%20made%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20interpret%20Ono%E2%80%99s%20instructions%20as%20seeds%20for%20the%20cultivation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Csocial%20imaginary%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20an%20imaginary%20system%20of%20ideas%2C%20values%2C%20orientations%20and%20practices%20that%20binds%20society%20together.%20Beyond%20%E2%80%9Ccreation%E2%80%9D%2C%20Ono%E2%80%99s%20instruction%20project%20is%20a%20catalyst%20for%20continuous%20social%20change%2C%20a%20process%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconstruction%E2%80%9D%20that%20leads%20to%20an%20alternative%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20instructions%20lead%20to%20a%20social%20balance%20between%20the%20individual%20and%20the%20collective%2C%20through%20reflective%20everyday%20acts.%20These%20small%20disruptive%20acts%20draw%20awareness%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20society%20is%20socially%20constructed%2C%20and%20so%20it%20is%20down%20to%20the%20power%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20radical%20imaginary%20to%20change%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOno%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20peace%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20over%20seven%20decades%2C%20Ono%E2%80%99s%20radical%20ideas%20have%20contributed%20to%20powerful%20social%20ideas%20such%20as%20peace%2C%20freedom%2C%20equality%20and%20democracy.%20Her%20persistent%20commitment%20to%20world%20peace%20is%20expressed%20through%20her%20conception%20of%20art%20as%20a%20radical%20imaginary%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOno%E2%80%99s%20instructions%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flickr.com%2Fphotos%2Fyokoonoofficial%2F2892207133%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cmeant%20for%20others%20to%20do%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20precisely%20what%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdoing%E2%80%9D%20do%20they%20enable%3F%20Works%20such%20as%20Shadow%20Piece%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CPut%20your%20shadows%20together%20until%20they%20become%20one%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Film%20No.%204%20(Bottoms)%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CString%20bottoms%20together%20in%20place%20of%20signatures%20for%20petition%20of%20peace%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20instruct%20people%20to%20play%2C%20but%20to%20play%20%E2%80%9Cwith%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%20%E2%80%9Cagainst%E2%80%9D%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOno%E2%80%99s%20playful%20works%20undermine%20the%20systemic%20causes%20that%20drive%20society%E2%80%99s%20problems%20and%20trigger%20processes%20of%20social%20imagining.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20you%20play%20an%20all-white%20chess%20set%20with%20an%20%E2%80%9Copponent%E2%80%9D%20(White%20Chess%20Set%2C%201966)%2C%20get%20undressed%20under%20a%20bag%20(Bag%20Piece%2C%201964)%2C%20or%20shake%20hands%20through%20a%20hole%20in%20a%20canvas%20(Painting%20to%20Shake%20Hands%2C%201961)%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstranger%E2%80%9D%3F%20This%20requires%20working%20in%20concert%20with%20the%20other%20and%20coming%20up%20with%20a%20new%20set%20of%20rules%20%E2%80%93%20initiating%20new%20social%20relations%20that%20lead%20to%20radically%20new%20modes%20of%20thought%20and%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEngaging%20the%20social%20imagination%20can%20contribute%20to%20changing%20the%20drives%20and%20consciousness%20of%20individual%20people%20who%20could%20collectively%20change%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20by%20imagining%20it%20not%20as%20it%20is%2C%20but%20as%20it%20ought%20to%20be.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20can%20construct%20the%20world%20they%20dream%20of.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fyokoono%2Fstatus%2F1295742125687087105%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3EAs%20Ono%20puts%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20dream%20you%20dream%20alone%20is%20only%20a%20dream.%20A%20dream%20you%20dream%20together%20is%20reality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOno%E2%80%99s%20distinct%20approach%20to%20the%20empowering%20social%20role%20of%20art%20galvanises%20people%20in%20many%20directions.%20To%20discover%20new%20constructive%20principles%20for%20creating%20spaces%20for%20critical%20thinking%20and%20artistic%20experimentation.%20For%20knowledge%20creation%20and%20political%20resistance.%20And%20to%20imagine%20an%20alternative%20world%20%E2%80%93%20because%20to%20%E2%80%9Cimagine%E2%80%9D%20is%20to%20embark%20on%20a%20process%20of%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGabriella%20Daris%20is%20completing%20a%20PhD%20in%20Philosophy%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Research%20in%20Modern%20European%20Philosophy%20(CRMEP)%2C%20Kingston%20University%20London.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fyoko-ono-music-of-the-mind-tate-show-explores-the-artists-radical-legacy-223939%3Futm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DLatest%2520from%2520The%2520Conversation%2520for%2520March%25201%25202024%2520-%2