b-health-minister-9164170%2F%5C%22%3Eas%20a%20result%20of%20pellet%20gun%20injuries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20several%20had%20their%20faces%20disfigured%20by%20the%20gunshots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShubkaran%20Singh%2C%20a%2021-year-old%20farmer%20from%20Bhatinda%2C%20died%20from%20head%20injuries%20last%20week%2C%20with%20his%20family%20and%20farmer%20groups%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Fcrime%2Fshubhkaran-singh-death-bullet-injury-farmers-protest-fir-details%5C%22%3Emaintaining%20he%20was%20shot.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Much%20before%20the%20protests%20began%2C%20the%20Haryana%20Police%E2%80%99s%20preparations%20gave%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20far%20the%20state%20would%20go%20to%20prevent%20a%20movement%20from%20taking%20shape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20DGP%20of%20Haryana%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fharyana-dgp-denies-using-pellet-guns-against-protesting-farmers%2Farticle67860605.ece%5C%22%3Edenied%20using%20pellets%20on%20farmers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20medical%20injuries%20sustained%20give%20us%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20spectacular%20nature%20of%20violence%20against%20farmers%20protesting%20peacefully%20at%20the%20Punjab-Haryana%20border%20crossings%20of%20Khanuari%20and%20Shambhu%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20instance%20of%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20in%20India%20was%20witnessed%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20in%202010.%20In%202016%2C%20following%20the%20protests%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20after%20the%20encounter%20of%20Hizbul%20commander%20Burhan%20Wani%2C%20the%20police%20resorted%20to%20excessive%20pellet%20actions%2C%20injuring%20hundreds%20of%20protesters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20a%20petition%20was%20filed%20in%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20High%20Court%20regarding%20the%20usage%20of%20pellet%20guns%2C%20and%20the%20court%20refused%20to%20put%20an%20interim%20stay%20on%20its%20use.%20In%20the%20year%202017%2C%20the%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20Bar%20Association%20petitioned%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20for%20a%20blanket%20prohibition%20on%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20weapons%2C%20which%20asked%20the%20high%20court%20to%20expedite%20the%20matter.%20It%20was%20in%202020%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Fj-k%2Fj-k-high-court-refuses-to-ban-use-of-pellet-guns-in-kashmir-53869%5C%22%3Ehigh%20court%20finally%20dismissed%20the%20petition%3C%2Fa%3E%20upholding%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20by%20the%20security%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20reasoned%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20protest%20is%20not%20peaceful%20and%20security%20personnel%20are%20attacked%20by%20violent%20mobs%2C%20they%20have%20to%20use%20force%20in%20self-defense.%E2%80%9D%20Further%2C%20regarding%20the%20nature%20of%20force%2C%20it%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20kind%20of%20force%20has%20to%20be%20used%20at%20a%20relevant%20point%20in%20time%20or%20in%20a%20given%20situation%20and%20place%20has%20to%20be%20decided%20by%20the%20persons%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20place%20where%20the%20attack%20is%20happening.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20rejected%20the%20appeal%20by%20referring%20to%20force%20mostly%20in%20vague%20terms%20without%20addressing%20the%20issue%20of%20pellets.%20However%2C%20it%20mentioned%20that%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20has%20formed%20an%20expert%20committee%20to%20look%20into%20the%20matter.%20The%20report%2C%20which%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20made%20public%2C%20did%20not%20prohibit%20its%20usage%20but%20recommended%20that%20it%20be%20used%20as%20a%20last%20resort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20is%20now%20pending%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20heard%20in%20April%20this%20year.%20The%20petition%20challenges%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20on%20account%20of%20them%20being%20%E2%80%98indiscriminatory%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20how%20they%20target%20people.%20What%20is%20meant%20by%20this%20%E2%80%98indiscriminate%E2%80%99%20nature%20is%20that%20when%20a%20pellet%20gun%20is%20fired%2C%20100%20pellets%20that%20are%20lethal%20are%20sprayed%20in%20all%20directions%2C%20where%20men%2C%20women%2C%20children%2C%20and%20even%20innocent%20bystanders%20watching%20the%20events%20are%20blinded%2C%20injured%2C%20and%20sometimes%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoctors%20treating%20pellet%20victims%20have%20stated%20that%20it%20maims%20a%20person%20forever%2C%20causing%20partial%20or%20complete%20blindness.%20The%20spread%20and%20proclivity%20for%20their%20usage%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20degree%20of%20destruction%20caused%2C%20are%20unparalleled%2C%20making%20them%20unsuitable%20for%20managing%20the%20crowd%20as%20their%20operators%20cannot%20effectively%20control%20their%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20%E2%80%98indiscriminate%E2%80%99%20character%20of%20pellets%20violates%20the%20UN%20Basic%20Principles%2C%20which%20specify%20that%20the%20use%20of%20force%20to%20disperse%20nonviolent%20unlawful%20assemblies%20should%20be%20avoided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDissecting%20the%20pellet%20and%20the%20law%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPellet%20guns%2C%20made%20of%20metals%20that%20resemble%20ball%20bearings%2C%20are%20classified%20as%20Kinetic%20Impact%20Projectiles%20(KIPs)%2C%20which%20include%20weapons%20that%20cannot%20be%20aimed%20at%20specific%20targets%20but%20scatter%20ammunition%20widely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20risks%20connected%20with%20KIPs%20include%20death%20or%20major%20injury%20to%20the%20head%2C%20upper%20body%2C%20or%20susceptible%20area%20if%20struck%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20projectiles%20penetrating%20the%20body%2C%20and%20a%20high%20risk%20of%20injuring%20innocent%20bystanders%20due%20to%20projectile%20inaccuracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20international%20law%2C%20the%20use%20of%20pellets%20is%20prohibited%20because%20it%20violates%20the%20norms%20of%20proportionality%20under%20international%20human%20rights%20law%20and%20customary%20international%20law.%20The%20UN%20Basic%20Principles%20on%20the%20Use%20of%20Force%20and%20Firearms%20by%20Law%20Enforcement%20Officials%2C%20adopted%20by%20the%20eighth%20United%20Nations%20Congress%20on%20Crime%20Prevention%20and%20Treatment%20of%20Offenders%20require%20the%20government%20and%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20to%20consider%20the%20ethical%20issues%20associated%20with%20the%20use%20of%20force%20and%20firearms%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20exercise%20restraint%20proportionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fharyana-dgp-claims-rubber-bullets-not-pellet-guns-used-on-protesting-farmers%5C%22%3EHaryana%20DGP%20Claims%20Rubber%20Bullets%2C%20Not%20Pellet%20Guns%2C%20Used%20on%20Protesting%20Farmers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20the%20development%20of%20non-lethal%20incapacitating%20weapons%20for%20use%20in%20specific%20scenarios.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20International%20Committee%20of%20the%20Red%20Cross%2C%20under%20rules%2070%20and%2071%2C%20prohibits%20the%20use%20of%20tools%20that%20are%20indiscriminate%20and%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20cause%20unnecessary%20pain%20or%20suffering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Committee%20of%20the%20Red%20Cross%20rules%2C%20even%20for%20warfare%2C%20do%20not%20accept%20attacks%20that%20may%20cause%20incidental%20loss%20of%20civilian%20life%2C%20injury%20to%20civilians%2C%20damage%20to%20civilian%20objects%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20thereof%20that%20is%20excessive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPellet%20action%20against%20the%20farmers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20are%20likewise%20constitutionally%20obligated%20to%20display%20fundamental%20restraint%20and%20act%20proportionally%20to%20their%20legitimate%20objectives%20that%20are%20to%20be%20achieved.%20It%20is%20consequently%20crucial%20to%20ask%20what%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20objective%20was%20in%20using%20force%20against%20the%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssuming%20it%20was%20to%20prevent%20the%20farmers%20from%20marching%20to%20Delhi%2C%20then%20the%20question%20remains%3A%20what%20if%20the%20farmers%20had%20crossed%20the%20border%20and%20arrived%20in%20Delhi%3F%20Have%20the%20farmers%20not%20demonstrated%20enough%20that%20their%20protests%20have%20been%20extremely%20peaceful%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20is%20completely%20aware%20that%20the%20protests%20are%20not%20intended%20to%20generate%20a%20public%20emergency%20or%20chaos%20in%20Delhi.%20The%202020%20farmer%20demonstrations%20have%20already%20given%20us%20the%20most%20powerful%20example%20of%20non-violent%20protests%20in%20the%20recent%20history%20of%20India.%20What%20explains%20the%20firing%20of%20tear%20gas%20shells%20from%20drones%20overhead%2C%20injuring%20hundreds%20of%20farmers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20elderly%20and%20have%20difficulty%20breathing%2C%20when%20a%20template%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20protest%20had%20already%20been%20established%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20question%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20asked%20here%20is%3A%20Was%20the%20use%20of%20cranes%2C%20boulders%2C%20and%20roadblocks%20to%20restrict%20the%20protestors%E2%80%99%20from%20exercising%20their%20constitutional%20rights%20to%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20assembly%20not%20a%20force%20that%20the%20state%20performed%20right%20before%20the%20protests%20had%20begun%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20deploying%20pellet%20guns%20that%20left%20protesters%20permanently%20disabled%20and%20at%20risk%20of%20death%2C%20the%20state%20breached%20its%20commitment%20to%20protect%20and%20preserve%20human%20life.%20These%20violated%20both%20the%20constitutional%20requirement%20to%20protect%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights%20to%20life%20and%20health%20as%20well%20as%20the%20international%20laws%20that%20forbid%20such%20use%20in%20conflict%2C%20let%20alone%20in%20peaceful%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA)%20is%20widely%20used%20to%20discredit%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%2C%20and%20it%20has%20become%20a%20standard%20instrument%20for%20criminalising%20dissent%20in%20democratic%20India.%20It%20is%20time%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20not%20let%20the%20usage%20of%20pellet%20guns%20be%20normalised%20in%20a%20peaceful%20citizen%20demonstration.%20Suppressing%20people%E2%80%99s%20movement%20with%20measures%20such%20as%20pellet%20guns%20assumes%20protestors%20are%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fem%3Eviolent%20and%20unorganised%20mob%E2%80%99%20and%20attempts%20to%20disorganise%20an%20organised%20group%20of%20civilian%20protestors%20by%20using%20excessive%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20must%20see%20through%20the%20recent%20usage%20of%20pellet%20guns%20in%20Manipur%20and%20Delhi%20borders%20against%20the%20protestors%20and%20strike%20it%20down%20immediately.%20It%20must%20now%20hear%20the%20long-overdue%20petition%20and%20prohibit%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20altogether%2C%20especially%20during%20civilian%20protests.%20This%20would%20reassert%20its%20constitutional%20obligation%20to%20protect%20and%20facilitate%20free%20expression%20and%20assembly%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKawalpreet%20Kaur%20is%20a%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709380750000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F08141152%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-08-at-1.00.13-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffarmers-protest-has-shown-that-sc-must-strike-down-the-use-of-pellet-guns-with-a-sense-of-urgency%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20international%20law%2C%20the%20use%20of%20pellets%20is%20prohibited%20because%20it%20violates%20the%20norms%20of%20proportionality%20under%20international%20human%20rights%20law%20and%20customary%20international%20law.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%2