y%20South%20Asian%20countries%20in%20(its%20performance%20towards)%20achieving%20its%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20that%20its%20economic%20process%20has%20not%20adequately%20rubbed%20off%20on%20the%20parameters%20linked%20to%20broad%20societal%20quality%20of%20life%20agendas%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20former%20UN%20undersecretary-general%20for%20economic%20and%20social%20affairs%2C%20Nitin%20Desai%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Findia-ranks-112th-on-progress-towards-un-mandated-sustainable-development-goals-in-2023%2Fcid%2F2004138%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20score%20of%2063.45%25%20in%202023%2C%20India%20marked%20a%20small%20improvement%20over%20the%20previous%20year%E2%80%99s%2060.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20specific%20parameters%20of%20%E2%80%9Creducing%20inequalities%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Clife%20on%20land%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20performance%20has%20deteriorated.%20Life%20on%20land%20relates%20to%20conserving%20biodiversity%2C%20where%20India%20is%20close%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20has%20also%20fared%20poorly%20on%20parameters%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Csustainable%20cities%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cequality%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cclean%20water%20and%20sanitation%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cpeace%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20strong%20institutions%E2%80%9D.%20Its%20performance%20in%20relation%20to%20%E2%80%9Cno%20hunger%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csustainable%20cities%20and%20communities%E2%80%9D%20has%20also%20stagnated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20its%20performance%20on%20%E2%80%9Cpoverty%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csustainable%20consumption%E2%80%9D%20indicators%20appears%20to%20have%20remained%20on%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20the%20UN%20adopted%2017%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20as%20a%20universal%20call%20to%20action%20to%20end%20poverty%20and%20prot